{{Infobox government agency | name = Estonian Weather Service | native_name = Riigi Ilmateenistus | type = department | seal = | seal_width = | seal_caption = | logo = | logo_width = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | formed = {{Start date and age|2013|06|01}} | preceding1 = Estonian Meteorological and Hydrological Institute | dissolved = | superseding1 = | jurisdiction = [[Government of Estonia]] | headquarters = [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]] | coordinates = {{Coord|59.423985|24.6997|region:EE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | motto = | employees = | budget = | minister1_name = [[Marko Pomerants]] | minister1_pfo = Minister of the Environment of Estonia | deputyminister1_name = Taimar Ala<ref name="kontaktid"/> | deputyminister1_pfo = Director of the Estonian Environment Agency | chief1_name = Priidik Lagemaa<ref name="kontaktid"/> | chief1_position = Vice Director of the Estonian Environment Agency | parent_department = Estonian Environment Agency | parent_agency = [[Ministry of Environment (Estonia)|Ministry of Environment]] | child1_agency = | website = {{URL|1=http://www.ilmateenistus.ee/?lang=en}} | footnotes = }}
The '''Estonian Weather Service''' ({{lang-et|Riigi Ilmateenistus}}) is the [[Estonia]]n national [[meteorology|meteorological]] service.
Estonian Weather Service is a department part of the Estonian Environment Agency, which in turn is under the responsibility of the [[Ministry of Environment (Estonia)|Ministry of Environment]].<ref name="kontaktid">{{cite web|title=Kontaktid|url=http://www.keskkonnaagentuur.ee/et/kontaktid|publisher=Estonian Environment Agency|accessdate=21 February 2016}}</ref>
Estonian Weather Service is a member of the [[World Meteorological Organization]] (WMO) and [[EUMETSAT|European Organisation for the Exploitation of Meteorological Satellites]] (EUMETSAT).
Before 1 June 2013, the department was a separate agency on its own known as the '''Estonian Meteorological and Hydrological Institute''' ('''EMHI''').<ref name="contact">{{cite web|title=Contact|url=http://www.ilmateenistus.ee/ilmateenistus/kontakt/?lang=en|publisher=Estonian Weather Service|accessdate=21 February 2016}}</ref>
Estonian Weather Service's webpage offers you 4day forecast (also in Russian and English), week forecast and month forecast (only in Estonian). Page also has a radar, model forecast and warnings.
