The '''Grand Comoro bulbul''' (''Hypsipetes parvirostris'') is a species of [[songbird]] in the [[bulbul]] family, Pycnonotidae.
It is found on the [[Comoro Islands]]. 
Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s. Until 2011, the [[Moheli bulbul]] was considered as a subspecies of the Grand Comoro bulbul.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldbirdnames.org/updates/archives/species-2-0-2-11/|title=Species  Version 2 « IOC World Bird List|website=www.worldbirdnames.org|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-30}}</ref> Alternative names for the Grand Comoro bulbul include the '''Comoro bulbul''' and '''Grand Comoro black bulbul'''.

